    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't that a bit of a circular argument though? if the people are starving or losing their homes because there's no safety net, the economy is basically already collapsed socially and politically. isn't \"fiscal responsibility\" just a way to justify cutting essential services that people actually need to survive?",
